text: Eiko Yasui (born 8 May 1971) is a Japanese volleyball player. She was part of the Japan women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 1994 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, and 1994 Asian Games, winning a bronze medal.. On a club level, she played with Kanagawa. == References == Category:1971 births Category:Japanese volleyball players Category:Living people
